    {
      "line": 19,
      "text": "ROBERT DAWSON"
    },
    {
      "line": 22,
      "text": "|. San Luis Drain, Kesterson National Wildlife Refuge, California (193)"
    },
    {
      "line": 23,
      "text": "The San Luis Drain carries wastewater to Kesterson from the toxic,"
    },
    {
      "line": 24,
      "text": "selenium-laden soils of California’s western San Joaquin Valley."
    },
    {
      "line": 26,
      "text": "In the 1980s, huge numbers of birds died, or were born deformed,"
    },
    {
      "line": 27,
      "text": "from this man-made disaster."
    },
    {
      "line": 33,
      "text": "2. Indians Fishing, Lahontan Reservoir, near Fallon, Nevada (194)"
    },
    {
      "line": 36,
      "text": "3. Stone Mother, Pyramid Lake, Nevada (|990)"
    },
    {
      "line": 38,
      "text": "In Paiute legend, a mother was overwhelmed with grief at losing her husband"
    },
    {
      "line": 39,
      "text": "and children. She knelt crying in the sand. The tears fell about her, forming a"
    },
    {
      "line": 40,
      "text": "puddle that grew larger and larger. She cried until all the water from her heart"
    },
    {
      "line": 41,
      "text": "and body was gone. She turned to stone. Her tears became Pyramid Lake."
    },
    {
      "line": 44,
      "text": "4. Spillway, Lake Berryessa, California (\\920)"
    },
    {
      "line": 45,
      "text": "When Lake Berryessa fills up, water cascades over this spillway rather"
    },
    {
      "line": 46,
      "text": "than over the top of the dam pictured on the right."
    },
    {
      "line": 49,
      "text": "3. Three Mile Slough Bridge, near Rio Vista, California (\\986)"
    },
    {
      "line": 51,
      "text": "| grew up on the edge of the Delta in California’s Central Valley. Summers"
    },
    {
      "line": 52,
      "text": "were very hot and winters produced this drearr-like and mysterious tule"
    },
    {
      "line": 53,
      "text": "fog that would blanket the ground for weeks. The Central Valley fog absorbs"
    },
    {
      "line": 56,
      "text": "pesticides from the air at a very high rate. Contaminated fog touches"
    },
    {
      "line": 57,
      "text": "everyone and everything in the valley."
    },
    {
      "line": 60,
      "text": "For information about Robert Dawson and Ellen Manchester’s Water in the West"
    },
    {
      "line": 61,
      "text": "Project, see Gossip (p. 122). Robert Dawson is represented by Swanstock (PO Box"
    },
